Sergio Aguero marked his 350th Manchester City game with two goals, as they defeated Southampton 3-1, to reach the Carabao Cup quarter-finals on Tuesday night. Nicolas Otamendi headed the current holders in front in the 20th minute, before Aguero struck in either half to seal victory. Jack Stephens’ grabbed a late consolation goal for the Saints, who they will face again in the Premier League this weekend. In other fixtures, Everton beat Watford 2-0, Leicester City won 3-1 at Burton Albion and Colchester United saw off Crawley Town 3-1. The rest of the quarter-finalists will be decided on Wednesday, when Liverpool host Arsenal and Chelsea clash with Manchester United. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.